This is a pinned copy of Califa's `schema/` + `skillcard/` packages (including
the `skillcard.harness` subpackage, dormant here — `make check` never runs
`skillcard eval`), plus the Jinja template and pyproject, so the public
cabinet's `make check` can validate and gate skill cards without a private-repo
CI secret. v0.8.0 enabled `skillcard badges` (consumed by the badge-serving CI
job, .github/workflows/badges.yml); v0.9.0 added `skillcard scorecard`, consumed
by `make scorecards` (scripts/build_scorecards.py) to render the per-skill and
rollup SVGs embedded in the READMEs; v0.9.1 cleans up those SVGs.

